REBALANCING\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b\fs22 \cf2 OBJECTIVE
\fs20 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 This tab illustrates the correlations between each indicator, sub-pillar, pillar, and sub index, and aggregation levels above it. For example, the INDICATOR table shows the correlation of each indicator with its sub-pillar, pillar, sub-index and index.\
\
Typically the aim in a composite indicator is to balance these correlations, so that each indicator makes a balanced contribution to the higher aggregation levels. To make adjustments, users can change the weights in the Adjusted Weights rows, and compare the correlation with the initial weights (those entered in the 
\b Database tab
\b0 , with the new correlations as a result of these adjusted weights.
\b \

\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\b\fs22 \cf2 STEP-BY-STEP\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs20 \cf0 1) 
\b0 Adjust the (positive) threshold for low correlation, if necessary - this will highlight cells with positive correlations below this value in orange. Negative correlations are highlighted in red.\

\b 2) 
\b0 Set adjusted weights for each indicator, sub-pillar, pillar and sub-index can be input in the light blue cells. If no adjustment is desired, set these as the initial weights.\

